1. Requirements
-----------------
ViennaSHE requires only
 - a not too dated C++ compiler (e.g. gcc 4.x.x),
 - the C++ Standard Template Library,
 - PETSc (https://petsc.org/
 - ViennaGrid (http://viennagrid.sourceforge.net/), and
 - ViennaCL (http://viennacl.sourceforge.net/)

For building the examples, CMake can be used.


2. Installation
-----------------

The first step is to extract the file:

Unix-based OS:
$> gunzip ViennaSHE-1.3.0.tar.gz
$> tar -xf ViennaSHE-1.3.0.tar
$> cd ViennaSHE-1.3.0

Detailed instructions for the various operating systems can obtained by opening the file
  ./doc/html/manual-page-installation.html
in your favorite browser. An online version is available at
  http://viennashe.sourceforge.net/doc/manual-page-installation.html


3. Project Layout
-----------------

---- ViennaSHE-1.X.X
   |
   |-- build/ - Build folder for the examples
   |
   |-- cmake/ - Auxiliary files for the CMake build system
   |
   |-- doc/ - HTML documentation
   |
   |-- examples/ - Tutorial and benchmarking applications
        |
        |-- data/ - Test meshes for the tutorials
        |
        |-- devices/ - Tutorial applications for different semiconductor devices
        |
        |-- libviennashe/ - How to use ViennaSHE as a shared C library
        |
        |-- python/ - Example usage of the Python wrappers
   |
   |-- libviennashe/ - The shared C-library wrapper
   |
   |-- python/ - The Python bindings for using ViennaSHE from Python
   |
   |-- src/ - Interface to the solvers used in ViennaSHE
   |
   |-- tests/ - Automated test suite for ViennaSHE
   |
   |-- viennacl/ - The library source code of ViennaCL
   |
   |-- viennagrid/ - The library source code of ViennaGrid
   |
   |-- viennashe/ - The library source code of ViennaSHE


4. Authors and Contact
------------------------

ViennaSHE was developed under the aegis of the 'Institute for Microelectronics' and the 'Institute for Analysis and Scientific Computing' at the 'Vienna University of Technology'.
It is supervised by Prof. Tibor Grasser and Prof. Ansgar J\"ungel and contains code contributed by Karl Rupp, Markus Bina, and Peter Lagger.

Please send any support requests to our mailing list at viennashe-support@lists.sourceforge.net
(feel free to sign up here first: https://lists.sourceforge.net/lists/listinfo/viennashe-support)

